Ad Text:
Our client, a leading retailer, is seeking a Data Steward to support their data governance and risk initiatives. This role is being re-opened following the previous incumbent moving on, with funding secured through the end of the financial year.
What You’ll Be Doing
Drafting and maintaining data management policies, standards, and frameworks
Supporting the operation of data councils and chapters, ensuring alignment to the organisation’s operating model
Providing oversight on data risk and ensuring compliance with governance frameworks
Partnering with stakeholders across the business to embed good data practices
Leveraging prior consulting experience to bring structure and best practice into data governance activities
What We’re Looking For
8–12 years of consulting experience (from firms such as KPMG, Deloitte, or EY)
Strong background in data governance and data risk management
Experience in policy writing and developing frameworks
Proven ability to work with senior stakeholders and influence decision-making
Knowledge of Collibra would be an advantage
Someone hands-on and pragmatic, not too senior but confident in delivering governance outcomes
Why Join This is a great opportunity to apply your consulting experience in a major retail organisation, helping to shape data governance practices and deliver value across the business. You’ll join a collaborative team and play a key role in embedding data stewardship as part of the organisation’s operating model.

We are partnering with a rapidly growing AI scale up that is redefining how organisations adopt artificial intelligence at scale. This is an opportunity to join a high calibre team building enterprise grade AI systems that deliver measurable business impact.

This role is ideal for a hands on AI practitioner who enjoys building, testing, and deploying intelligent systems in real world environments. You will work closely with senior team members and cross functional stakeholders, owning core modelling and deployment tasks that directly influence customer outcomes.
The Opportunity As a Mid Level AI Data Scientist, you will play a key role in delivering scalable AI and machine learning solutions across complex business environments. You will contribute to end to end solution development, from experimentation through to production deployment.
You will work in a fast paced, collaborative setting where innovation, technical depth, and commercial impact are equally valued.
Key Responsibilities
Design, build, and deploy machine learning and AI solutions that solve genuine business problems
Support the development and optimisation of LLM and NLP based systems, including fine tuning, prompt engineering, embeddings, and retrieval augmented generation
Contribute to scalable ML pipelines and assist with model monitoring, evaluation, and cloud based deployment
Run structured experiments, evaluate model performance, and continuously improve AI systems
Collaborate with product, engineering, and business stakeholders to translate requirements into technical solutions
Leverage both structured and unstructured data to generate insights and measurable commercial outcomes
What You Bring
3 to 5 years of experience in data science, AI, or machine learning
Strong Python capability and solid SQL skills
Hands on experience with NLP or LLM based applications
Exposure to MLOps and model deployment concepts
Experience working with cloud platforms such as AWS, GCP, Azure, or Databricks
Strong analytical and problem solving skills
Clear communication skills, with the ability to translate technical findings for both technical and non technical audiences
Why Apply
You will join a business that partners deeply with enterprise clients to embed AI directly into complex operational environments. Their approach blends advanced machine learning, NLP, and LLM expertise with a strong focus on security, privacy, and measurable return on investment.
If you are looking to move beyond experimentation and into real enterprise AI delivery, this is an opportunity to work on meaningful, production grade AI systems that genuinely augment how organisations operate.

Are you a data science expert passionate about AI innovation and stakeholder influence? We’re seeking a Staff Data Scientist to drive cutting-edge AI advancements while working closely with executives and non-technical stakeholders to shape AI adoption and impact.
This role is ideal for someone who thrives at the intersection of technical excellence and business strategy, ensuring AI solutions deliver real value across the organisation.

About the Role
As a Lead or Principal Data Scientist, you will play a crucial role in developing and deploying machine learning models, optimising AI performance, and influencing key business decisions. Your expertise in NLP, LLMs, and MLOps will drive innovation, while your ability to communicate complex AI concepts to executives will ensure AI initiatives align with business objectives.
This is a high-visibility role where you’ll work across teams, bridging the gap between technical execution and business strategy—helping senior stakeholders understand the power of AI and how to apply it effectively.

Key Responsibilities
AI Strategy & Business Alignment – Work closely with executives and business leaders to integrate AI-driven solutions into company strategy.
Technical Leadership – Design, develop, and optimise machine learning models, with a focus on NLP and large-scale AI applications.
Executive Stakeholder Influence – Translate complex AI concepts into clear, actionable insights for non-technical leaders.
MLOps & AI Engineering – Implement best practices for model deployment, monitoring, and performance optimisation at scale.
Data-Driven Decision Making – Drive high-impact AI initiatives by leveraging advanced analytics on structured and unstructured data.
Research & Innovation – Stay ahead of AI trends, applying cutting-edge techniques to enhance business performance and operational efficiency.
What You’ll Bring
8+ years of experience (Staff Level) in data science, AI, and machine learning, with strong expertise in NLP and LLMs.
A track record of engaging with C-suite and senior business stakeholders, influencing AI strategy and execution.
Expert-level Python and SQL skills, with deep experience in building and deploying machine learning models at scale.
Hands-on experience with MLOps best practices, cloud-based AI solutions, and large-scale data processing.
A strategic mindset, with the ability to translate AI advancements into business impact.
Exceptional communication and influencing skills, able to simplify complex concepts for non-technical audiences.
What’s in It for You?
Work at the forefront of AI innovation, shaping strategy at a high-growth tech company.
Partner directly with executives and business leaders to drive enterprise-wide AI transformation.
Join a team that values curiosity, technical excellence, and real-world AI applications.
Hybrid work model (Sydney-based, 2-3 days in-office).
If you’re a highly experienced AI professional who can influence at an executive level while delivering cutting-edge AI solutions, we’d love to hear from you. Apply now!

Several opportunities

Immediate start possible - location: port of Brisbane 4/5 days a week

KOM Consulting is looking for (contract) Senior Business Analysts, based in Brisbane, to join our team.

We have multiple opportunities in the coming week, including an immediate opening for a SBA to join our client and assist in the implementation of a Safety System. This project is delivered at the Port of Brisbane and requires 4-5 days of on-site presence.

Besides the usual BA skills, we're looking for the following non-negotiables:

* Proactive and accountable attitude: you're able to work through ambiguity and follow work through to completion.

* Strong delivery mindset: you are focused on completing and finalising documentation, not just contributing.

* Onsite presence to support workshops, stakeholders, and delivery momentum

* Comfortable switching context between multiple work streams, tasks, and stakeholders

* Relevant Business Analyst experience on complex delivery projects, ideally system or transformation programs

* Commitment to the allocated hours and ownership of deliverables

* Flexibility to travel if and when required by clients

* Minimum 4-5 years of Business Analyst experience on complex delivery projects, ideally system or transformation programs

* Australian work rights required - candidates must be eligible to work in Australia without sponsorship

Oracle NetSuite is the leading integrated cloud business software suite, which combines business accounting, ERP, CRM and ecommerce software.  NetSuite helps companies manage core business processes with a single, fully integrated system in the cloud.  NetSuite is literally transforming business around the globe by providing a cloud-based, unified system that delivers unprecedented capabilities to drive business forward.

Picture yourself building a successful career at Oracle-NetSuite — working alongside hard-working, dedicated, innovative, and driven people, staying invested in our customers and the community, and helping fast-growing mid-sized organisations and larger enterprises achieve their business goals.

Only Oracle brings together the data, infrastructure, applications, and expertise to power everything from industry innovations to life-saving care. And with AI embedded across our products and services, we help customers turn that promise into a better future for all. Discover your potential at a company leading the way in AI and cloud solutions that impact billions of lives.

True innovation starts when everyone is empowered to contribute. That’s why we’re committed to growing a workforce that promotes opportunities for all with competitive benefits that support our people with flexible medical, life insurance, and retirement options. We also encourage employees to give back to their communities through our volunteer programs.

We’re committed to including people with disabilities at all stages of the employment process. If you require accessibility assistance or accommodation for a disability at any point, let us know by emailing accommodation-request_mb@oracle.com or by calling 1-888-404-2494 in the United States.

Oracle is an Equal Employment Opportunity Employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, gender identity, disability and protected veterans’ status, or any other characteristic protected by law. Oracle will consider for employment qualified applicants with arrest and conviction records pursuant to applicable law.

What You’ll Do

As a leading contributor within the practice, this mid-senior-level consulting position provides consistently high quality and innovative solution leadership to a project team.

You will:

Be a Lead Functional Consultant/Delivery Manager and have extensive NetSuite ERP implementation/optimisation expertise
Analyse business needs to help ensure the Oracle NetSuite solution meets the customer’s objectives by combining leading practices, product knowledge, and business acumen
Resolve complex customer issues by recommending and delivering solutions
Work closely with the rest of the customer success team by quickly assessing client needs, developing innovative plans to solve their problems and implementing these plans to the client's satisfaction
Have a passion for business and the associated Cloud technologies, as well as advanced analytical problem-solving skills, applied to help clients find creative ways to run their businesses more effectively
Ability to conduct functional requirements gathering and solution workshops
Strong communication and presentation skills

Other responsibilities include:

Leading the optimisation aspects of engagement(s) ensuring high quality solutions within constraints of time and customer prioritisations.
Providing direction and mentoring to customer teams, and effectively influencing customer leadership on key decisions.
Being responsible for managing clients in post go-live environments.
Being adept at managing the delivery of NetSuite application functionality.
Working with technical and performance experts at NetSuite to get the best outcomes for your customer.

Finding new ways to constantly improve the satisfaction and loyalty of our clients is a top priority. In this role, you will often be working under pressure, working with several customers simultaneously and striving to meet customer expectations.

Successful candidates should have demonstrated experience in gathering customer business requirements and strong business analysis skills.  Good functional knowledge of NetSuite and an understanding of accounting principles is desirable.  Excellent interpersonal skills are essential.

Location and Travel

The role is located in Australia, Singapore, Hong Kong or New Zealand, with the ability to travel up to 15%.

Career Level - IC3

About BHP 


At BHP we support our people to grow, learn, develop their skills and reach their potential. With a global portfolio of operations, we offer a diverse and inclusive environment with extraordinary career opportunities. Our strategy is to focus on creating a safe work environment where our employees feel strongly connected to our values and objectives, and where the capability of our people is key to our success.

Come and be a part of this success.

About the Role


BHP’s Performance and Data Analytics team is responsible for undertaking analysis and providing insights to drive maintenance productivity and performance across our assets. Our activities range from identifying maintenance performance gaps, deriving actionable insights, formulating strategies and implementing improvement projects.    

As a Specialist Data Science, you will be key driver in improving BHP’s maintenance productivity. Leveraging cutting-edge big data technologies and a rich library of datasets, the Specialist Data Science will develop quantitative analysis of current performance, identify drivers of failure and predictions on future performance. Furthermore, the role functions as a key advisor to decision makers as we develop strategies to mitigate risk and improve outcomes for our customers.  

The Specialist Data Science will working collaboratively alongside other data scientists, performance and improvement specialists, and operations and business subject matter experts to level up BHP’s maintenance productivity.

This is a Brisbane based role offering permanent opportunity working Monday to Friday. Flexible working options are available.

In this role, you will:

Investigate complex problems using a structured problem-solving approach
Write code and conduct analysis utilising a range of technologies and techniques
Enable performance improvement by producing actionable insight from data
Confidently present ideas, results, and recommendations to stakeholders at all organisational levels

About You


You will have a related tertiary qualification and demonstrated experience in supporting business improvement strategies and initiatives.

You will:

Have strong analytical, critical thinking and creative problem-solving skills
Have experience programming in Python and SQL to:
Build descriptive, diagnostic, predictive and prescriptive modelling
Perform structured and unstructured data mining
Apply machine learning and statistical modelling techniques
Be a collaborative team player that is results orientated
Thrive in dynamic, fast paced teams.

Other highly regarded experience includes:

Have experience in exploring and proposing new ideas that may have benefits for the business
Apply Large Language Model to solve real-world NLP and automation use cases
Asset Management experience in mining, manufacturing, or similar heavy industry
Experience working in engineering and/or management consulting
Experience using Power BI
